ant's position that not everyone should be able to obtain everything they want in the game.  (Someone probably has their famous Vision *TM one liner if so toss it up please.)<br>
<br>
We as the Brell community have decided that everyone that wants something in the game SHOULD have a fair shot at it.<br>
<br>
Thus, raid rules that we conjure up, that are fair to everyone, will conflict the major Vision *TM of Varent.(ie if they wanted everyone to have the Venril stones and leggings they would have made VS spawn 24hours)<br>
<br>
Where are the problems or perceived problems in out current Raid Scheduling system?  Venril Sathir? Trakanon (if not now soon)?<br>
<br>
I personally think the VS problem will go away once the pressure for epics is off.  However, with the number of druids and rangers that NEED the stone, and given the one week spawn time, this will take quite a while.<br>
<br>
Here is my suggestion for a bandaid for the current 9 month list regarding VS raids.  Identify INDY rangers and druids that are signed up, for the sole purpose of claiming a stone.  See if there can be some arrangement made with those who are raiding before these INDY's to get them a stone.  What does this do?  Well your raid gives up one stone to an Indy (ranger or druid).  That Indy then removes their name from the list.  This causes the list to shorten and your next raid comes again much quicker.  The key here is to take the &quot;INDY raid to claim a stone&quot; pressure off the list.  Once this is done things should start moving again much quicker.<br>
<br>
Garam Ebonhands<br>
